subsection.def:
applicant
                (申請人)
                means the party making the interlocutory application;

paragraph.content:
a decision, a determination or an order that dismisses a cause or matter on
                    the determination of a question of law or construction of a document without a
                    full trial of the action;

section.def:
applicant (申請人),
            in relation to an application for leave referred to in rule 60, means the
            person who applies for the leave;

paragraph.content:
in relation to an application referred to in rule 74 or
                        83, means the person who files an originating notice of
                    application under that rule;

